"&#xa0;\nWritten evidence submitted by Michael Hannis and Sian Sullivan&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nExecutive Summary &#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;AuthorsMichael Hannis is an AHRC-funded Postdoctoral Researcher in the \nGeography, Environment and Development Studies\n \ndepartment at\n \nBirkbeck\n College, \nUniversity of London.\n&#xa0;\nSian Sullivan is Senior Lecturer \nin Environment and Development, department of \nGeography, Environment and Development Studies, \nBirkbeck\n College, \nUniversity of London, \nand a Co-Investigator for the \nLeverhulme\n Centre for the Study of Value\n. (\nwww.sed.manchester.ac.uk/research/LCSV/\n)\n&#xa0;\nWe are \nwriting jointly but in a personal capacity, and \nthis submission does not represent\n the view\ns\n of \nBirkbeck\n \nCollege \nor \nof \nany other body\n. \nWe submit this evidence in order to enable the Committee to consider information and insights gained through ongoing academic research, some of which is as yet unpublished. This includes Sian Sullivan’s supervision of current PhD research into the unfolding of the DEFRA offsets pilots and policy, conducted as part of a studentship funded by the \nLeverhulme\n Trust.\n&#xa0;&#xa0;Evidence&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nA\ns for the latter, it is our understanding that this assumption has been substantially undermined by DEFRA’s own research.\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;Recommendations&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nIn \ndeciding whether to proceed with BO:\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nIf BO does proceed:\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n14 October 2013\n&#xa0;\n \nOffsetting Nature\n?\n is\n freely available online at \nwww.greenhousethinktank.org/files/greenhouse/home/Offsetting_nature_inner_final.pdf\n \nTyldesley\n, \n&#xa0;\nD \n&#xa0;\net \n&#xa0;\nal,\n \n&#xa0;\n2012, \n&#xa0;\nEffectiveness \n&#xa0;\nof